The paper proposes a traffic signal control system that uses deep reinforcement learning methods, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep convolutional neural networks for processing traffic data suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of the proposed system in a traffic microsimulator and the use of Q-learning with experience replay suggest that the paper may also fall under the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks for processing traffic data suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
